  "description": "We were coming down the drainage and heard a bird calling and at first thought short-tailed wren....the chip chip...chip chip. \u00a0I had just heard Winter Wren calls at another location recetnly and thought they sounded similar but higher pitched and less \"harsh\". \u00a0I pulled up Merlin when we first heard it calling and it said Pacific. \u00a0Linday quickly spotted the bird calling from on a fallen log over the creek in some thick willows and I was able to get photos. \u00a0The bird was noticably rufous below than typical Winter Wren. \u00a0https://ebird.org/checklist/S124277787",
